2026-04-19 18:26:05 | DEBUG    | utils | JSON_llm raw response BEFORE parsing: {"learnings":["Residual connections and layer normalization are crucial for stabilizing deep neural networks and enhancing their performance by allowing easier gradient flow and reducing training time (p. 3).","Scaled dot-product attention in neural networks involves computing the dot product of query with keys, scaling by the inverse of the square root of the key dimension, followed by a softmax to obtain weights. This technique enhances the focus of the network on specific parts of the input sequence (p. 3).","End-to-end memory networks enable the model to leverage an external memory component, enhancing its capacity to remember long-term dependencies, which is particularly beneficial in tasks requiring sequential decisions (p. 12).","Dropout is an effective regularization method to prevent overfitting in neural networks by randomly dropping units during training, thereby making the network robust and ensuring diverse feature learning (p. 12).","Language models can exploit subword units to effectively handle rare words, improving translation quality and generalization by utilizing smaller, more frequent components of longer words (p. 12)."],"followUpQuestions":["What are the specific mechanisms by which dropout prevents overfitting in neural networks?","How do the modifications in self-attention influence the model's performance on sequence generation tasks?"]}
